results.name: default/mysql-service

error.Text: Service default/mysql-service has event Failed to create endpoint for service default/mysql-service: endpoints "mysql-service" already exists

results.details:
Error: The error indicates that an endpoint for the service "mysql-service" already exists, preventing the creation of a new one.

Solution: 
1. Check existing endpoints: `kubectl get endpoints`.
2. Delete the existing endpoint: `kubectl delete endpoints mysql-service`.
3. Recreate the service if needed: `kubectl apply -f service.yaml`.

results.name: kube-system/kube-dns

error.Text: Service kube-system/kube-dns has event Failed to create endpoint for service kube-system/kube-dns: endpoints "kube-dns" already exists

results.details:
Error: The error indicates that the endpoint for the kube-dns service already exists, causing a conflict.

Solution: 
1. Check existing endpoints: `kubectl get endpoints -n kube-system`.
2. Delete the conflicting endpoint: `kubectl delete endpoints kube-dns -n kube-system`.
3. Recreate the service if needed.
